#. HTML: <section class="sutta" id="sn4.1"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn4.1:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 4 "
msgstr "Linked Discourses 4 "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. VAR: 1. Paṭhamavagga → āyuvaggo (bj) | āyuvaggo paṭhamo (pts2)
msgctxt "sn4.1:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga "
msgstr "1. Life Span "

#. HTML: </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn4.1:0.3"
msgid "1. Tapokammasutta "
msgstr "1. Mortification "

#. HTML: </h1></div><p><span class="evam">
#. REF: pts1ed1.103, pts2ed1.231, sc1
msgctxt "sn4.1:1.1"
msgid "Evaṃ me sutaṃ—"
msgstr "So I have heard. "

#. HTML: </span>
msgctxt "sn4.1:1.2"
msgid "ekaṃ samayaṃ bhagavā uruvelāyaṃ viharati najjā nerañjarāya tīre ajapālanigrodhamūle paṭhamābhisambuddho. "
msgstr "At one time, when he was first awakened, the Buddha was staying near Uruvelā at the root of the goatherd’s banyan tree on the bank of the Nerañjarā River. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
msgctxt "sn4.1:1.3"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavato rahogatassa paṭisallīnassa evaṃ cetaso parivitakko udapādi: "
msgstr "Then as he was in private retreat this thought came to his mind, "

msgctxt "sn4.1:1.4"
msgid "“mutto vatamhi tāya dukkarakārikāya. "
msgstr "“I am truly freed from that grueling work! "

msgctxt "sn4.1:1.5"
msgid "Sādhu mutto vatamhi tāya anatthasaṃhitāya dukkarakārikāya. "
msgstr "Thank goodness I’m freed from that pointless grueling work. "

# NOTE: I follow BB in adopting Bj reading; it is the Lectio difficilior
#. VAR: Sādhu vatamhi mutto bodhiṃ samajjhagan”ti → sādhu ṭhito sato bodhiṃ samajjhaganti (bj, pts1-2) | sādhu vatamhi satto bodhisamajjhagūti (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn4.1:1.6"
msgid "Sādhu vatamhi mutto bodhiṃ samajjhagan”ti. "
msgstr "Thank goodness that, steadfast and mindful, I have attained awakening.” "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc2
msgctxt "sn4.1:2.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā bhagavato cetasā cetoparivitakkamaññāya yena bhagavā tenupasaṅkami; upasaṅkamitvā bhagavantaṃ gāthāya ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "And then Māra the Wicked, knowing what the Buddha was thinking, went up to him and addressed him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: pts2ed1.232, sc3
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.1"
msgid "“Tapokammā apakkamma, "
msgstr "“You’ve departed from the practice of mortification "

# NOTE: Read yena, duh.
#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.2"
msgid "ye na sujjhanti māṇavā; "
msgstr "by which humans purify themselves. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.3"
msgid "Asuddho maññasi suddho, "
msgstr "You’re impure, but think yourself pure; "

#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: suddhimaggā aparaddho → suddhimaggamaparaddho (bj, pts1-2) | suddhimaggaṃ aparaddho (s1-3, km)
msgctxt "sn4.1:3.4"
msgid "suddhimaggā aparaddho”ti. "
msgstr "you’ve strayed from the path of purity.” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc4
msgctxt "sn4.1:4.1"
msgid "Atha kho bhagavā “māro ayaṃ pāpimā” iti viditvā māraṃ pāpimantaṃ gāthāhi ajjhabhāsi: "
msgstr "Then the Buddha, knowing that this was Māra the Wicked, replied to him in verse: "

#. HTML: </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. REF: sc5
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.1"
msgid "“Anatthasaṃhitaṃ ñatvā, "
msgstr "“I realized that it’s pointless; "

# NOTE: This phrase occurs thrice. here, Thag 3.1, and Snp.252 at Snp 3.2. There we have “Ye vāpi loke amarā bahū tapā” which I can’t help feeling would make better sense if amara meant “endless”. However, i will retain the accepted meaning.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: amaraṃ tapaṃ → aparaṃ tapaṃ (s1-3, pts1-2, mr)
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.2"
msgid "yaṃ kiñci amaraṃ tapaṃ; "
msgstr "all that mortification in search of immortality "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.3"
msgid "Sabbaṃ natthāvahaṃ hoti, "
msgstr "is as futile "

# NOTE: See BB for readings.
#. HTML: <br>
#. VAR: dhammani → dhammaniṃ (pts1) | phiyārittaṃ vajahmani (pts2) | jammaniṃ (mr)
msgctxt "sn4.1:5.4"
msgid "phiyārittaṃva dhammani. "
msgstr "as oars and rudder on dry land. "

#. HTML: </p><p>
#. REF: sc6
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.1"
msgid "Sīlaṃ samādhi paññañca, "
msgstr "Ethics, immersion, and wisdom: "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.2"
msgid "Maggaṃ bodhāya bhāvayaṃ; "
msgstr "by developing this path to awakening "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.3"
msgid "Pattosmi paramaṃ suddhiṃ, "
msgstr "I attained ultimate purity. "

#. HTML: <br>
msgctxt "sn4.1:6.4"
msgid "Nihato tvamasi antakā”ti. "
msgstr "You’re beaten, terminator!” "

#. HTML: </p></blockquote><p>
#. REF: sc7
msgctxt "sn4.1:7.1"
msgid "Atha kho māro pāpimā “jānāti maṃ bhagavā, jānāti maṃ sugato”ti, dukkhī dummano tatthevantaradhāyīti. "
msgstr "Then Māra the Wicked, thinking, “The Buddha knows me! The Holy One knows me!” miserable and sad, vanished right there."

#. HTML: </p></article></section></body></html>
